Package: CountClust
Type: Package
Title: Aimed at clustering and visualization of counts data
Version: 0.99.0
Date: 2016-03-13
Authors@R: c(
    person("Kushal", "Dey", email = "kkdey@uchicago.edu", role = c("aut","cre")),
    person("Joyce", "Hsiao", email = "joyce.hsiao1@gmail.com", role = "aut"),
    person("Matthew", "Stephens", email = "stephens999@gmail.com", role ="aut"))
Maintainer: Kushal K Dey <kkdey@uchicago.edu>
Description: Takes any count table data as input, performs data preprocessing,
    and uses topic model clustering (due to `maptpx` package of Matt Taddy) and
    produces cluster visualization in the form of Structure plot representation.
Depends:
    R(>= 3.2.0),
    ggplot2
URL: https://github.com/kkdey/CountClust
License: GPL (>= 2)
LazyData: true
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports: maptpx, RColorBrewer, plyr (>= 1.7.1), gtools, cowplot, limma, parallel, reshape2
Suggests:
    knitr, BiocStyle, roxygen2  
VignetteBuilder: knitr
biocViews: RNASeq, GeneExpression, Clustering, Sequencing, StatisticalMethod,
    Software, Visualization
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
